üîç Insights from Data:
Customers with month-to-month contracts and electronic check payments showed higher churn risk.

Longer tenure customers were less likely to churn (strong loyalty effect).

Customers subscribed to Fiber optic internet churned more compared to DSL or no internet service.

Additional services like TechSupport, OnlineSecurity, and DeviceProtection correlated with lower churn probability.

Customers with higher monthly charges tend to show an increased churn tendency.

Most churned counts is found in No service and the least churned count is in fibre optic services of lines,internet and phone services

Online backup lets to increase retention rate and same is with online security.

Customers using Electronic Check show a higher churn compared to other payment methods.

Credit Card and Bank Transfer users are relatively more loyal.
